== 2. The Integrated Model (The "Smart Loop")
<the-integrated-model-the-smart-loop>
To map this logically, you should view the relationship as a
#strong[Control Loop] where Bloom's Taxonomy dictates the "intelligence"
of the PUDAL cycle.

There are two ways to view this relationship:

=== A. The "Reflexive" PUDAL (Low-Level Bloom)
<a.-the-reflexive-pudal-low-level-bloom>
If the system is simple (automation), the PUDAL cycle stays at the
bottom of Bloom's: \* #strong[P:] Detects heat (Remember). \*
#strong[U:] Interprets as "Too Hot" (Understand). \* #strong[D:] Selects
pre-set rule "Turn on Fan" (Basic Application/Selection). \* #strong[A:]
Turns on Fan (Apply). \* #strong[L:] Checks if temp dropped (Basic
Evaluation).

=== B. The "Cognitive" PUDAL (High-Level Bloom)
<b.-the-cognitive-pudal-high-level-bloom>
If the system is smart (AI/Human Expert), the PUDAL cycle reaches the
top of Bloom's: \* #strong[P:] Detects market anomaly (Remember). \*
#strong[U:] Interprets as a new emerging trend (Understand). \*
#strong[D:] #strong[Synthesizes] a new investment strategy to exploit
the trend (#strong[Create/Design];). \* #strong[A:] Executes the trade
(#strong[Apply];). \* #strong[L:] #strong[Critiques] the strategy's
validity against global variables to update its mental model
(#strong[Evaluate];).

== 3. Visualizing the Relation as a Map
<visualizing-the-relation-as-a-map>
If you were to draw a knowledge map of this relationship, it would look
like a #strong[Spiral];.

+ #strong[The Axis:] The vertical pole is Bloom's Taxonomy (Depth).
+ #strong[The Cycle:] PUDAL is a circle winding around the pole.
+ #strong[The Movement:]
  - As you move from #strong[P] to #strong[U];, you climb slightly.
  - At #strong[D];, you spike up to the highest levels
    (Creating/Analyzing).
  - At #strong[A];, you drop down to practical ground level (Applying).
  - At #strong[L];, you climb back up to judge the whole process
    (Evaluating).

#strong[Summary for your Model:] The #strong[\[D\]] and #strong[\[L\]]
phases correspond to the "Higher Order Thinking Skills" (HOTS) in
Bloom's Taxonomy, while #strong[\[P\]];, #strong[\[U\]];, and
#strong[\[A\]] correspond to "Lower Order Thinking Skills" (LOTS). A
truly "Smart" system is defined by how robust its #strong[D]
(Design/Create) and #strong[L] (Evaluate) phases are.
